ACKNOWLEDGEMENT

This project (babel-canvas) was developed by ParadigmShift, Lda. It is built on the
ParadigmShift fork of the Babel-Swarm framework and its HyParView membership and
eager-push gossip protocols, originally developed in the Computer Systems Group of
NOVA LINCS at NOVA School of Science and Technology (NOVA FCT),
https://novasys.di.fct.unl.pt, in the context of the TaRDIS European project,
https://www.project-tardis.eu.

The protocols and framework this project builds on are described in:

  J. Leitão, J. Pereira and L. Rodrigues, "HyParView: A Membership Protocol for
  Reliable Gossip-Based Broadcast," 37th Annual IEEE/IFIP International Conference
  on Dependable Systems and Networks (DSN'07), Edinburgh, UK, 2007, pp. 419-429,
  doi: 10.1109/DSN.2007.56.
  Public version: https://asc.di.fct.unl.pt/~jleitao/pdf/dsn07-leitao.pdf

  P. Fouto, P. Á. Costa, N. Preguiça and J. Leitão, "Babel: A Framework for
  Developing Performant and Dependable Distributed Protocols," 2022 41st
  International Symposium on Reliable Distributed Systems (SRDS), Vienna, Austria,
  2022, pp. 146-155, doi: 10.1109/SRDS55811.2022.00022.
  Public version: https://asc.di.fct.unl.pt/~jleitao/pdf/fouto-srds22.pdf

Any permitted use or redistribution must retain this copyright notice and the
acknowledgement above in all copies or substantial portions of the Software.

